markdown: <::logo: Kona Coffee Kona Coffee A stylized coffee cup with coffee beans and leaves, next to the brand name.::> COFFEE CHIFFON CAKE 2 eggs, 1 t. salt separated 1/2 c. cold strong 1½ c. sugar Kona coffee 2¼ c. sifted 1/2 c. milk cake flour 1/8 t. baking soda 1 T. baking 2 t. vanilla powder 1/3 c. salad oil Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar. Beat until stiff and glossy. Sift remaining sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together. Make a well in center of dry ingredients. Combine coffee, milk, baking soda and vanilla. Add salad oil and one-half the coffee mixture to dry ingredients; beat 1 min. at medium speed or 150 strokes by hand. Add remaining coffee mixture and egg yolks and beat additional min. Fold egg whites into batter gently but thoroughly. Pour into two greased and floured 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350- degrees for 30-35 minutes. Remove from pans; cool. Split each layer into two layers. Fill and frost with any com- patible frosting. Yield: 8-10 servings.
